                        <li><strong>Focus & Concentration:</strong> Difficulty sustaining attention, easily distracted.</li>
                        <li><strong>Organization & Time Management:</strong> Struggling with planning, prioritizing, and meeting deadlines.</li>
                        <li><strong>Impulsivity:</strong> Acting without thinking, difficulty with self-control.</li>
                        <li><strong>Emotional Regulation:</strong> Experiencing intense emotions, mood swings.</li>
                        <li><strong>Motivation:</strong> Challenges with starting or completing tasks, especially if they're not highly stimulating.</li>
                    </ul>
                    <p>But ADHD also comes with incredible strengths like creativity, hyperfocus on interests, high energy, and out-of-the-box thinking. Coaching helps you leverage these strengths while developing strategies for the challenges.</p>
